<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="290" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[113,753,1948,2100]" lastBlockId="8.[811,1453,838,1182]" pageId="8" pageNumber="290">
This is the most updated checklist of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1912" box="[564,719,1949,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Metapocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,719,1949,1972]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="290">Metapocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingCountry box="[160,290,1980,2004]" name="Philippines" pageId="8" pageNumber="290">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation box="[309,400,1980,2004]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="9.[136,191,189,211]" captionText="Table 1. Updated checklist of Metapocyrtus in the Philippines." pageId="8" pageNumber="290">Table 1</tableCitation>
) since 
<bibRefCitation author="Yap SA" box="[493,619,1980,2004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="290" pagination="249 - 260" refId="ref14060" refString="Yap SA (2008) Checklist of the Metapocyrtus complex (Curculionidae: Entiminae: Pachyrrhynchini) of the Philippines. Asia Life Sciences, 17 (2): 249 - 260." type="journal article" year="2008">Yap, 2008</bibRefCitation>
. A total of seven subgenera and 258 species are listed. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Waterhouse, 1842)" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Metapocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans" subGenus="Metapocyrtus">
<emphasis box="[605,752,2013,2036]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="290">Metapocyrtus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[123,282,2045,2068]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="290">Metapocyrtus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[305,393,2044,2068]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="290">elegans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse GR" box="[413,631,2044,2068]" pageId="8" pageNumber="290" pagination="302 - 311" refId="ref13972" refString="Waterhouse GR (1842) Descriptions of new species of coleopterous insects belonging to the genus Apocyrtus, collected by Hugh Cuming, Esq., in the Philippine Islands. Annals Magazine of Natural History, 9: 302 - 311." type="journal article" year="1842">Waterhouse, 1842</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded from Polillo Island. Based on the list, 50% of species are only found on Luzon island, 22.09% of species have only been recorded from Mindanao, and 19.77% are found on Visayas. Another 5.04% are Philippine endemics with no specific island or locality records. 0.78% are species found on both Mindanao-Luzon, and 1.55% are species found on Mindanao-Visayas, both one species found on Visayas- Luzon and Luzon-Visayas-Mindanao, respectively. The data implies that surveys and collections were more concentrated on Luzon compared to other islands. Our recent survey in Mount Hamiguitan reveals that there are more unknown species that await discovery.
</paragraph>
